hung their stockings at my fireplace I ate breakfast over there and they all had dinner and supper at my house. We just sat around the fireplace and talked over old friends I wondered if your ears burned and ^we played the Phonograph. ate candy and <del>wound</del> wound up by taking a "hinkles" at bed tiem to ward off any bad effect of the christmas dinners By the way, we had roast chicken and stuffing mashed potatoes & gravy sweet potatoes Lima beans rolls & beets cabbage salad. Plum pudding with piles of whipped cream. And we wished for your. Mrs. Brown is going to Bancroft to fix up the place for sale again. She had to take it back the people are leaving it in awful condition. Just as soon as it sells again she will come here. Lisben! My dear it is a long -it down here and you must plan to come as soon as school closes and get back just in time to begin in the fall. I won't make company of you. She will do just as we would were you not here and I'll be so glad to have you I am sure you will have a better time than if we made a fuss over you. The children are talking about you coming and Monda will just as glad as I you will love baby Alice John starts on his trip East and last of this month. Will be in Omaha in March. 
